I don't think that it really
mean anything necessarily.

38:40.784 --> 38:42.718
What about you?

38:42.853 --> 38:46.186
Your songs are pretty--
pretty profound.

38:46.223 --> 38:47.884
What are you trying to say?

38:49.927 --> 38:52.020
I'm not-- I'm not trying
to say anything.

38:53.764 --> 38:57.063
I sing about what I see.

38:59.113 --> 39:01.633
He represented
everything that Andy didn`t

39:02.097 --> 39:06.369
and I just really
wanted to free myself.

39:10.933 --> 39:12.730
The music was just hypnotic.

39:12.769 --> 39:15.465
- I just think he's so maximal.
- Isn't he?

39:15.505 --> 39:18.201
And he just has that power.
You know people who have that power.

39:18.241 --> 39:20.436
- Like Superman?
- You can't really explain why it is.

39:20.476 --> 39:22.535
It just is.

39:22.578 --> 39:25.479
Well, what do you say to someone
like that? I mean, he's just so famous.

39:25.515 --> 39:27.642
- We didn't really talk, you know.
- Oh, you didn't?

39:27.684 --> 39:29.447
It was just nice to meet him.
Andy, what do you think of this?

39:29.485 --> 39:31.476
Tres chic or tres fou?

39:31.521 --> 39:33.512
Oh, tres chic,
definitely.

39:33.556 --> 39:36.753
Well, I have to watch my spending.
Especially on clothes.

39:36.793 --> 39:38.488
You know, I already
stopped wearing underwear.

39:38.528 --> 39:40.894
Shit, what other sacrifices
do I have to make?

39:40.930 --> 39:43.057
Who do you think you are?

39:43.099 --> 39:45.966
Your family is so rich.

39:46.002 --> 39:48.766
I mean, you're living
on Easy Street.

39:48.805 --> 39:51.740
Oh!

39:51.774 --> 39:53.605
Oh, Mama would love this.

39:53.643 --> 39:55.076
I can buy it for you.

39:55.111 --> 39:57.136
Oh no, you need
to watch your spending.

39:57.180 --> 40:00.411
So, tell me more things.
Who else was he there with?

40:00.450 --> 40:02.577
I don't really remember that,
you know?

40:02.618 --> 40:04.245
But it was just something
about those lyrics.

40:04.287 --> 40:06.812
What he was saying
was really poignant.

40:06.856 --> 40:08.517
Like he really
had something to say.

40:08.558 --> 40:10.219
What?

40:10.259 --> 40:13.092
I was just saying
that he really had something to say.

40:13.129 --> 40:15.063
- How much is this?
- Seven.

40:15.098 --> 40:16.929
- $7?
- $7.

40:16.966 --> 40:18.263
Oh no, that's too much.

40:20.103 --> 40:22.367
Well, I could
give you $4.

40:26.752 --> 40:29.346
James, dear, what are you
doing here so early?

40:29.388 --> 40:31.322
- I...
- Sit down.

40:31.357 --> 40:34.758
We had an appointment at my office
at noon, Miss Sedgwick. It's 2:30.

40:34.794 --> 40:37.695
You've known me since
I was three, James. Call me Edie.

40:37.730 --> 40:40.824
Your...

40:40.867 --> 40:42.767
spending, Miss Sedgwick.

40:42.802 --> 40:44.770
You're going to be
bankrupt soon.

40:44.804 --> 40:47.170
James, you take life
too seriously.

40:47.206 --> 40:49.106
How could I possibly
be bankrupt?

40:49.142 --> 40:51.007
My grandfather
invented the elevator.

40:51.043 --> 40:54.376
Then you should be familiar
with the concept of up and down.

40:54.413 --> 40:57.814
When you got here,
your trust fund--

40:57.850 --> 40:59.147
thank you.

40:59.185 --> 41:01.949
Your trust fund was up.

41:03.689 --> 41:07.125
After a year and a half,
it's almost in the basement.

41:09.328 --> 41:12.786
- Oh shit.
- What, what, what?

41:12.832 --> 41:15.027
Well, what about all
the money that I'm making?

41:15.067 --> 41:17.194
Well,
you keep spending it.

41:19.238 --> 41:21.103
Your father
is very upset with you

41:21.140 --> 41:23.506
cavorting with drug addicts

41:23.543 --> 41:25.340
and fringe elements.

41:25.378 --> 41:28.404
You tell Fuzzy for me that those are
some very talented people.

41:28.447 --> 41:30.711
If you don't
change your friends,

41:30.750 --> 41:32.945
you'll get nothing from him.

41:35.221 --> 41:36.848
Rich, will you make sure
the oven's off?

41:36.889 --> 41:38.880
I'm sorry, I have to go.

42:01.380 --> 42:04.247
Oh, looks like Cupid's
been busy as a bull dyke.

42:04.283 --> 42:06.274
You look beautiful, honey.

42:08.588 --> 42:10.954
Hello.

42:10.990 --> 42:12.651
What are you doing?

42:12.692 --> 42:14.683
Thought you weren't
gonna paint any more.

42:16.429 --> 42:18.397
Oh, look, it's Judy Garland.

42:18.431 --> 42:21.229
Wouldn't it be funny if it turned out
she was really a man?

42:21.267 --> 42:22.825
Wouldn't it be funny if it turned out

42:22.868 --> 42:24.358
Gerard was really a man?

42:24.403 --> 42:25.870
When you get through sucking on that,

42:25.905 --> 42:27.566
come over
and see for yourself.

42:27.607 --> 42:31.099
Only if I can record the slurps.

42:31.143 --> 42:35.045
Oh, Andy, Sam called. He's sending
a limo for us for the show tonight.

42:35.081 --> 42:36.548
I hear rock stars like limos.

42:39.518 --> 42:42.578
I think it's just delicious
that Edie has a boyfriend.

42:42.622 --> 42:44.817
I'm not looking
for anything like that.

42:44.857 --> 42:46.848
Okay.

42:52.598 --> 42:55.362
Don't be jealous, Andy.
He's nothing like you.

42:55.401 --> 42:59.098
Oh no, I'm not. I've just never made it
with a rock star before.

42:59.138 --> 43:00.867
- It must be neat.
- I'm not making it--

43:00.906 --> 43:03.841
Why do you do that?
Why do you have to make me feel guilty?

43:03.876 --> 43:06.344
I hate it when people
make me feel bad.

43:06.379 --> 43:08.847
Well, you lied to me.
You said you didn't talk to him.

43:08.881 --> 43:10.974
- And then that picture in the paper...
- Andy, this is absurd.

43:11.017 --> 43:12.746
It was a photograph.

43:12.785 --> 43:15.345
You know, we barely met.
You meet people all the time.

43:15.388 --> 43:17.117
Do you fuck them?

43:17.156 --> 43:20.819
Well, I just think sex
is too abstract anyway.

43:33.708 --> 43:35.403
Andy, what do you think
about the war in Vietnam?

43:35.443 --> 43:37.570
I don't know. Ask Edie.
What do you think, Edie?

43:37.612 --> 43:40.137
Well, we prefer
"I Dream of Jeannie."

43:40.181 --> 43:41.648
Andy, in the story of your life,

43:41.682 --> 43:43.343
who would you want
to play Andy Warhol?

43:43.384 --> 43:45.875
Oh, Edie. She's so perfect.
She does everything better than me.

43:45.920 --> 43:48.480
- Hi.
- Hello.

43:48.522 --> 43:50.786
Andy, I need
to talk to you.

43:50.825 --> 43:52.656
I've gotten myself
into a little pickle

43:52.693 --> 43:55.491
and I was just wondering if you could
maybe pay me for some of my work?

43:55.529 --> 43:57.258
Edie, you know the movies
haven't made any money yet.

43:57.298 --> 43:58.765
So you just need
to be patient.

43:58.799 --> 44:01.063
Well, I can't be patient.
I have nothing to live on.

44:01.102 --> 44:02.729
- Andy, you and I both know...
- Sam.

44:02.770 --> 44:04.761
...that you are
never giving up painting.

44:04.805 --> 44:07.035
You've just been saying that
to get publicity.

44:07.074 --> 44:09.065
- Well, guess what?
- What?

44:09.110 --> 44:11.169
- It worked.
- Great.

44:11.212 --> 44:13.737
Come on, everyone
wants to meet you.

44:13.781 --> 44:15.772
This way.

44:26.994 --> 44:29.724
Hello, kitty-kat.

44:29.764 --> 44:33.200
Hello.

44:33.234 --> 44:35.566
That's a wonderful scarf.

44:35.603 --> 44:37.935
Thank you.
Left my tux in the shop.

44:39.540 --> 44:41.235
You here to buy a painting?

44:42.777 --> 44:46.269
Tell me, why are all these cats gonna
pay a fortune for a soup can?

44:46.313 --> 44:47.712
I mean...

44:47.748 --> 44:50.216
You just have to look
beyond the obvious.

44:50.251 --> 44:52.583
Am I stupid, or...

44:52.620 --> 44:54.588
I don't get it.
Am I stupid?

44:54.622 --> 44:57.648
You're being a little stupid.
I mean, don't you think it's intriguing?

44:57.692 --> 44:59.250
Not just a little bit?

44:59.293 --> 45:02.194
You know, it may
just be a painting,

45:02.229 --> 45:04.629
but it's an idea.

45:04.665 --> 45:07.828
And the man behind that idea
is what's interesting.

45:09.303 --> 45:13.364
I think the man has got his priorities
all out of whack.

45:14.709 --> 45:17.177
Whole world's burning up
and this cat's making...

45:17.211 --> 45:19.372
gods out of garbage.

45:19.413 --> 45:20.903
Well, the whole world
may be burning up,

45:20.948 --> 45:23.644
but that doesn't mean
that we have to be cynical.

45:24.933 --> 45:27.299
Got the whole world on
a string, don't you?

45:29.204 --> 45:32.537
But inside there...

45:32.574 --> 45:35.634
well, it's as empty
as your friend's soup can.

45:43.318 --> 45:46.219
I'll see you around...

45:47.555 --> 45:49.546
superstar.

45:59.801 --> 46:02.531
Well, you're just so smart, Chuck.

46:02.570 --> 46:04.265
I just think you should
start directing.

46:04.305 --> 46:06.205
I mean, you do
the camera so good.

46:06.241 --> 46:09.142
We always need people
like you just to make things happen.

46:09.177 --> 46:12.044
Well, I mean, I'm really
just here for Edie, you know?

46:12.080 --> 46:14.844
Oh. Well, it's just such a pity

46:14.883 --> 46:17.249
that she should get all the attention
when you're the one who found her.

46:20.655 --> 46:22.179
I hope she still wants
to do more movies.

46:22.223 --> 46:23.485
She does.

46:23.525 --> 46:25.083
We-- we do,
we love movies.

46:25.126 --> 46:26.684
I mean, in fact,
I had this--

46:26.728 --> 46:29.253
I just don't know
if she's being...

46:29.297 --> 46:31.561
well, I mean, you know her
better than me.

46:31.599 --> 46:33.829
But, it seems like when
the camera's on sometimes

46:33.868 --> 46:35.301
she just doesn't seem...

46:37.005 --> 46:40.406
I don't know, I just wouldn't
want it to be disappointing.

46:40.442 --> 46:41.602
It won't.

46:41.643 --> 46:44.203
I can have her say
anything you want.

46:44.245 --> 46:46.873
She trusts me more
than anyone.

46:46.915 --> 46:48.610
Oh.

46:58.751 --> 47:02.517
"Beauty Number Two,"
an Andy Warhol production.

47:02.555 --> 47:05.888
Daddy, will you
pass me my martini?

47:06.892 --> 47:09.486
- Edie?
- Yes, Chuckles?

47:10.796 --> 47:13.094
Chuckles-- didn't I
give you that name?

47:13.132 --> 47:15.896
Edie, do you
like horses?

47:15.935 --> 47:18.335
Horses have whiskers.

47:18.370 --> 47:21.305
Yes, horses.
Do you ride?

47:21.340 --> 47:24.832
Since I was a little girl,
I've just adored them.

47:24.877 --> 47:27.345
Daddy taught me to ride
before I could walk.

47:27.379 --> 47:28.471
My first horse...

47:28.514 --> 47:30.948
Your father was
a handsome man?

47:30.983 --> 47:33.577
Oh, Fuzzy?

47:33.619 --> 47:35.644
He still is.

47:35.688 --> 47:38.885
How about your brothers? They were
quite attractive, too, weren't they?

47:38.924 --> 47:41.722
They must have had
a lot of women then.

47:41.760 --> 47:44.320
Wha--?

47:44.363 --> 47:46.888
Did they find
you attractive?

47:46.932 --> 47:50.026
Of course.
I was their family.

47:50.069 --> 47:52.936
Did you find them
attractive?

47:56.475 --> 47:59.273
- Do you...
- Can you change the question?

47:59.311 --> 48:03.111
find Gino attractive? That's-- that's
what I was going to ask you, Edie.

48:03.148 --> 48:05.878
Gino?

48:05.918 --> 48:08.716
He's devastatingly handsome,
isn't he?

48:08.754 --> 48:10.312
Kiss him.

48:15.661 --> 48:17.754
Are you scared?

48:28.507 --> 48:30.031
Come on, Edie.
Like you mean it.

48:40.519 --> 48:43.545
Gino, she likes when
you get rough.

48:43.589 --> 48:46.319
She likes those tough men.

48:46.358 --> 48:49.156
Strong men are what turn you on,
isn't that right, babycakes?

48:49.194 --> 48:50.422
No.

48:50.462 --> 48:53.295
Not like
your brother, Minty.

48:53.332 --> 48:56.028
Your father wasn't
so keen on him, was he?

48:57.236 --> 48:59.431
Who was he keen on? You?

49:01.407 --> 49:03.807
Okay, get off!
Enough!

49:14.787 --> 49:16.584
Andy, are we finished?

49:16.622 --> 49:19.113
No, Edie,
we're still rolling.

49:27.906 --> 49:30.306
Sedgwick.

49:36.915 --> 49:38.678
Edie Sedgwick!

49:39.851 --> 49:41.785
Hello.

50:38.816 --> 50:40.943
How'd a nice chick
like you get mixed up

50:40.985 --> 50:42.816
in the whole
acting racket?

50:42.853 --> 50:45.481
It was
"Breakfast At Tiffany's."

50:46.957 --> 50:50.017
You know that poster with Audrey
and her hair's pulled back

50:50.061 --> 50:52.791
and she's smoking through
the black cigarette holder?

50:54.598 --> 50:56.122
You want to live
in a movie?

50:56.167 --> 50:58.499
I never saw
the movie.

50:58.536 --> 51:00.834
So then you haven't
read the book, huh?

51:00.871 --> 51:03.499
Well, Audrey
isn't in the book.

51:04.809 --> 51:07.107
Book's a bit different.

51:08.946 --> 51:11.608
Book's about a working girl

51:11.649 --> 51:13.344
and a writer.

51:13.384 --> 51:15.784
An artist.

51:15.820 --> 51:19.916
You see, the artist steals
the girl's stories,

51:19.957 --> 51:22.858
makes a fortune,

51:22.893 --> 51:25.259
and the girl doesn't
get anything.

51:27.598 --> 51:31.329
Why do you have
such a problem with Andy?

51:31.368 --> 51:33.302
Because of what
he worships.

51:33.337 --> 51:36.829
And what about you? I mean,
I saw your face in those flashbulbs.

51:36.874 --> 51:39.707
You pretend to be
some sort of crusader,

51:39.744 --> 51:41.678
but I saw you
basking in it.

51:41.712 --> 51:44.044
Oh, don't get us confused,
sister, all right?

51:44.081 --> 51:46.015
Those bulbs, they get
a message out.

51:46.050 --> 51:48.848
What-- what exactly
is the message...

51:48.886 --> 51:51.184
aside from
"Look at me"?

51:53.023 --> 51:55.253
Nah, I'm just
a guitar player.

51:55.292 --> 51:56.691
- That's all.
- No no.

51:56.727 --> 52:00.185
You're an overpaid prophet
and I'm a poor little rich girl.

52:01.932 --> 52:04.400
Lady, you don't know
shit about shit.

52:04.435 --> 52:07.461
Open your eyes, you know? Take a look
at the world around you, okay?

52:07.505 --> 52:09.905
- It's very easy for you to say that...
- It's not all Park Avenue.

52:09.940 --> 52:11.874
- You do know that, don't you?
- ...from your wonderful,

52:11.909 --> 52:14.139
very glorified position
where you have your cars

52:14.178 --> 52:15.873
and your houses
and your fucking bike.

52:15.913 --> 52:17.471
You think I give a shit
about any of this?

52:17.515 --> 52:19.608
- I think it's obvious you do.
- You think I actually care?

52:19.650 --> 52:21.777
It's not real, babe.

52:44.608 --> 52:46.633
- Big house, huh?
- Big house.

52:46.677 --> 52:48.770
- Big family, too?
- Big family.

52:48.813 --> 52:50.804
Tell me about
your house.

52:50.848 --> 52:52.406
Mmm.

52:55.052 --> 52:57.748
We lived on a ranch.
We lived on two ranches

52:57.788 --> 52:59.255
in California.

52:59.290 --> 53:01.224
- Two ranches?
- Two ranches with--

53:01.258 --> 53:02.657
Must have been
a big family.

53:02.693 --> 53:04.354
It was a big family.
We had horses

53:04.395 --> 53:06.363
and cattle and we had--

53:06.397 --> 53:08.388
Lots of brothers
and sisters?

53:08.432 --> 53:11.424
We had eight brothers
and sisters.

53:11.468 --> 53:14.665
Now I have six
brothers and sisters.

53:16.907 --> 53:19.273
Well, what happened
to the other two?

53:21.378 --> 53:24.074
Minty...

53:25.950 --> 53:28.043
hanged himself

53:28.085 --> 53:30.053
at a place
called Silver Hill,

53:30.087 --> 53:32.146
which was sort of...

53:32.189 --> 53:34.350
a rehabilitation center.

53:34.391 --> 53:37.827
And Bobby...

53:37.862 --> 53:40.763
- Jesus.
- ...who was my elder brother

53:40.798 --> 53:43.767
ran his bike into a bus
on Fifth Avenue.

53:46.570 --> 53:49.698
But the funny thing
was was that I was in a--

53:49.740 --> 53:53.471
a car accident on the same--
it was New Year's Eve,

53:53.510 --> 53:57.344
and I-- well, he died,

53:57.381 --> 54:00.782
and-- and I didn't die.

54:00.818 --> 54:02.843
Babe.

55:52.062 --> 55:53.825
I was out with a couple
of heavies tonight.

55:53.864 --> 55:55.354
We talked about you
all evening.

55:55.399 --> 55:56.832
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah, guess who?

55:56.867 --> 55:59.062
- Diana Vreeland?
- No.

55:59.103 --> 56:00.798
- John Lennon?
- No.

56:00.838 --> 56:02.396
Edie Sedgwick?

56:03.574 --> 56:05.542
No, I haven't seen her.

56:05.576 --> 56:07.510
Don't know where
she is.

56:07.544 --> 56:09.944
Hey, you wanna hear
my new idea for a movie?

56:12.216 --> 56:13.945
Think I can invite her
for dinner?

56:13.984 --> 56:16.714
- Who?
- Edie.

56:16.754 --> 56:18.551
You wanna introduce her
to your mother?

56:18.589 --> 56:21.057
Why?

56:21.091 --> 56:23.184
Well, I hadn't thought--
I don't know.

56:23.227 --> 56:24.717
Might be nice.

56:24.762 --> 56:27.458
Jeez, Andy, you must really miss her.

56:27.498 --> 56:29.796
You never invite
anybody else over.

56:29.833 --> 56:32.233
Oh, cut it out.
You can't be that mean.

56:32.269 --> 56:34.464
Well, you never
invited me over.

56:34.505 --> 56:36.939
You need to lose
25 lbs first.

56:36.974 --> 56:39.465
My mother's not gonna feed you.
She's nastier than you are.

56:39.510 --> 56:41.774
She is not!

56:51.522 --> 56:53.285
I draw too, like Andy.

56:53.323 --> 56:54.881
Oh, you do?

56:54.925 --> 56:58.224
My husband work in
coal mine back then, yeah?

56:58.262 --> 57:00.594
And he very very
good-looking.

57:00.631 --> 57:02.496
Beautiful white hair.

57:02.533 --> 57:05.696
Every girl want this boy,
but he want me.

57:05.736 --> 57:08.227
- But I no want.
- Well, why didn't you want him?

57:08.272 --> 57:09.603
- I 15.
- Oh.

57:09.640 --> 57:12.905
But then one day,
he bring chocolate...

57:14.945 --> 57:17.345
...for purposes to
marry him.

57:17.381 --> 57:20.976
So for this candy,
I marry him.

57:23.053 --> 57:24.315
Oh!

57:24.354 --> 57:27.881
You make my Andy
so very happy.

57:27.925 --> 57:29.119
Oh.

57:29.159 --> 57:31.354
Oh, my special boy.

57:32.529 --> 57:34.827
With you, I think,

57:34.865 --> 57:37.493
all his skin blotches
go away.

57:37.534 --> 57:39.297
Mama, dost.

57:39.336 --> 57:40.860
Let me help you
with that.

57:40.904 --> 57:43.168
You the boss,
applesauce.

57:44.975 --> 57:47.500
You know, Andy, I've been spending
a lot of time with Billy.

57:47.544 --> 57:49.409
And I think that the more
I think about it,

57:49.446 --> 57:50.777
I really think that
you should meet.

57:50.814 --> 57:52.338
You'd really like
each other.

57:52.382 --> 57:53.713
Why would he want
to meet me?

57:53.750 --> 57:55.775
Well, because
you're a genius.

57:55.819 --> 57:58.014
And he's a genius.
Well, isn't he a genius, Julia?

57:58.055 --> 57:59.647
Oh, my boy a genius.

57:59.690 --> 58:01.920
Can you imagine how--
I mean, if we made a movie or something,

58:01.959 --> 58:04.018
wouldn't that be fun,
how explosive that would be?

58:04.061 --> 58:05.790
I just think if we
took him to The Factory

58:05.829 --> 58:08.229
everybody would respond very well.
Plus, he'd look beautiful--

58:08.265 --> 58:10.699
Edie, I just wanted to
get that for you.

58:10.734 --> 58:12.929
I know it's only $50,

