1:18:17.505 --> 1:18:19.029
fuck me last night

1:18:19.074 --> 1:18:22.874
doesn't mean that he
can take my silver.

1:18:22.911 --> 1:18:25.471
Did he film it?

1:18:25.513 --> 1:18:29.142
Yes, and you were great.

1:18:33.822 --> 1:18:37.815
- Are you done?
- Yeah, that's a wrap.

1:18:39.961 --> 1:18:42.259
- How do I look?
- You look groovy.

1:18:42.297 --> 1:18:44.595
Hey, Edie,

1:18:44.632 --> 1:18:46.463
can he borrow
your coat?

1:18:46.501 --> 1:18:49.493
That looks really
good on you.

1:18:49.537 --> 1:18:50.868
Thanks.

1:18:52.273 --> 1:18:54.798
All right, sweets,
I gotta go.

1:18:54.843 --> 1:18:56.310
Don't-- don't go.

1:18:56.344 --> 1:18:59.472
Don't leave me now.

1:18:59.514 --> 1:19:02.312
Maybe I'll come back later.

1:19:02.350 --> 1:19:05.478
Don't forget to blow out
all these candles.

1:19:07.155 --> 1:19:08.952
God, maybe you should
just sort of--

1:19:12.660 --> 1:19:15.060
Ciao.

1:19:18.500 --> 1:19:21.663
- Take off her coat, man.
- She said I could borrow it.

1:19:21.703 --> 1:19:24.695
No no no. Either you take it off
or I'm gonna take it off for you.

1:19:24.739 --> 1:19:27.606
- It's your choice.
- She just said that he could borrow--

1:19:27.642 --> 1:19:30.167
Take off the fucking coat!

1:19:30.211 --> 1:19:32.372
Hey, man,

1:19:32.414 --> 1:19:34.712
just mellow out, man.

1:19:34.749 --> 1:19:36.478
Now get the fuck
out of here.

1:19:36.518 --> 1:19:39.316
- Get the fuck out of here!
- Okay.

1:19:39.354 --> 1:19:42.551
We were just leaving,
man.

1:19:44.335 --> 1:19:47.634
Syd, is that you?

1:19:54.611 --> 1:19:56.442
Let me see.

1:19:58.182 --> 1:19:59.740
What are you doing?

1:19:59.783 --> 1:20:03.446
I said it all to him.

1:20:03.487 --> 1:20:04.715
I told him.

1:20:08.625 --> 1:20:10.252
I-I said it to Andy.

1:20:10.294 --> 1:20:14.253
I said it all to him.
Is that why you're here?

1:20:14.298 --> 1:20:18.064
Are we going upstate like he said?
'Cause if we are,

1:20:18.102 --> 1:20:20.866
I just need to put
a few things into a bag.

1:20:20.904 --> 1:20:22.565
He's out of town,
all right?

1:20:22.606 --> 1:20:24.801
But maybe,
maybe when he gets back.

1:20:24.842 --> 1:20:26.707
All right?

1:20:28.045 --> 1:20:31.674
Did-- did my father
call you?

1:20:31.715 --> 1:20:33.114
Is that why--

1:20:33.150 --> 1:20:35.710
is he gonna lock me
up again?

1:20:35.753 --> 1:20:37.050
No.

1:20:37.087 --> 1:20:40.181
Syd, will you stay--

1:20:40.224 --> 1:20:43.352
- stay the night with me?
- No.

1:20:43.394 --> 1:20:45.385
Edie.

1:20:47.297 --> 1:20:49.492
Lately, I--

1:20:52.102 --> 1:20:55.128
I feel like
I'm gonna die.

1:20:55.172 --> 1:20:56.901
You're not
gonna die, Edie.

1:20:59.143 --> 1:21:02.442
You're gonna be fine.
I promise.

1:21:02.479 --> 1:21:05.175
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1:21:08.152 --> 1:21:11.747
Hey, how about I buy
you something to eat?

1:21:11.789 --> 1:21:14.553
Can I do that?

1:21:18.562 --> 1:21:21.929
Looks like an accident.
It may be a while.

1:21:23.167 --> 1:21:25.431
Where are we going, Syd?

1:21:27.204 --> 1:21:29.798
I want to show
you something.

1:21:34.044 --> 1:21:37.036
Do you remember
that girl?

1:21:37.081 --> 1:21:38.639
Huh?

1:21:41.251 --> 1:21:43.048
That's--

1:21:43.087 --> 1:21:45.453
what was I thinking?

1:21:45.489 --> 1:21:49.016
The only reason I ever
went to that class was because of you.

1:21:50.394 --> 1:21:52.089
It's true.

1:21:54.498 --> 1:21:57.058
Do you remember her?

1:22:07.344 --> 1:22:09.335
No.

1:22:17.721 --> 1:22:19.348
Edie!

1:22:27.798 --> 1:22:31.734
I'm not saying that
anyone else is responsible.

1:22:31.768 --> 1:22:33.360
I made decisions,

1:22:33.403 --> 1:22:35.394
life decisions
that I regret.

1:22:37.608 --> 1:22:41.009
But I really feel
like I can do this.

1:22:42.379 --> 1:22:44.006
I can stay
off the drugs,

1:22:44.047 --> 1:22:46.174
and I realize that it will
be a battle every day,

1:22:46.216 --> 1:22:49.344
but so far

1:22:49.386 --> 1:22:51.445
so good, right?

1:22:53.123 --> 1:22:54.886
But I'm home.

1:22:54.925 --> 1:22:58.122
Santa Barbara
is my home.

1:23:00.764 --> 1:23:03.562
And I have a small show.
Did I tell you that?

1:23:03.600 --> 1:23:05.363
I mean,
it's nothing major.

1:23:05.402 --> 1:23:09.395
It's just in a frame shop,
but it's something.

1:23:52.416 --> 1:23:55.977
I just think people forgot what emotions
were supposed to be.

1:23:56.019 --> 1:23:58.146
I mean,
it's too hard to care.

1:23:58.188 --> 1:24:00.850
I mean, you know,
I still care,

1:24:00.891 --> 1:24:04.019
but it would just be so
much nicer not to care.

1:24:04.061 --> 1:24:06.621
It's just easier
being detached.

1:24:06.663 --> 1:24:08.756
What about Edie?

1:24:08.799 --> 1:24:11.461
Oh, what about Edie?
I haven't seen her in years.

1:24:11.501 --> 1:24:13.526
You know she died
yesterday?

1:24:13.570 --> 1:24:15.561
Oh, yeah.

1:24:15.606 --> 1:24:19.474
Do you think your breakup had something
to do with that detachment?

1:24:19.509 --> 1:24:21.477
Well, it wasn't
a breakup.

1:24:21.511 --> 1:24:25.242
I mean, that makes
it sound like we were--

1:24:25.282 --> 1:24:28.445
I mean, this is gonna
be really hard if we have to-- if--

1:24:32.022 --> 1:24:34.013
You know, it was
just so long ago.

1:24:34.057 --> 1:24:37.151
I mean, I hardly
knew her at all, so...

1:24:46.903 --> 1:24:49.838
I wonder if people
are gonna remember us.

1:24:49.873 --> 1:24:52.341
- What, when we're dead?
- Yeah.

1:24:52.376 --> 1:24:55.675
I think people will talk about how
you changed the world.

1:24:55.712 --> 1:24:58.510
I wonder what they'll say about you

1:24:58.548 --> 1:25:00.482
in your obituary.

1:25:00.517 --> 1:25:02.781
- I like that word.
- Nothing nice, I don't think.

1:25:02.819 --> 1:25:05.117
Oh, no, come on. It'd say,

1:25:05.155 --> 1:25:07.385
"Edith Minturn Sedgwick,

1:25:07.424 --> 1:25:09.392
beautiful artist
and actress..."

1:25:09.426 --> 1:25:11.394
"And all-around loon."

1:25:11.428 --> 1:25:13.658
"Remembered for setting
the world on fire..."

1:25:13.697 --> 1:25:16.860
"And escaping the clutches
of her terrifying family."

1:25:16.900 --> 1:25:19.494
"Made friends
with everybody and anybody..."

1:25:19.536 --> 1:25:22.505
"Creating chaos
and uproar wherever she went.

1:25:22.539 --> 1:25:24.837
Divorced as many times
as she married,

1:25:24.875 --> 1:25:27.639
she leaves only
good wishes behind."

1:25:29.212 --> 1:25:31.578
That's nice, isn't it?

1:25:44.027 --> 1:25:46.518
Edie seemed
to understand from the beginning

1:25:46.563 --> 1:25:48.292
her life
was going to be short.

1:25:48.332 --> 1:25:49.731
She was a blip on
the radar suddenly.

1:25:49.766 --> 1:25:51.495
It just blew out everybody.

1:25:51.535 --> 1:25:53.901
You walk into a room
and Edie was there.

1:25:53.937 --> 1:25:55.598
Edie was what you saw.

1:25:55.639 --> 1:25:59.439
There was something
so vulnerable about Edie.

1:25:59.476 --> 1:26:03.310
She was a person
that everybody adored

1:26:03.347 --> 1:26:04.939
and kind of worshipped,

1:26:04.981 --> 1:26:07.814
but you knew that she was
basically fragile.

1:26:07.851 --> 1:26:09.512
Time sort of stopped
when you were with her.

1:26:09.553 --> 1:26:11.748
She was
an exquisite creature.

1:26:11.788 --> 1:26:14.518
She had sort of a gamine look.
Very long legs,

1:26:14.558 --> 1:26:17.527
very pale face,
very pale lips.

1:26:17.561 --> 1:26:19.290
And a waif, in a way.

1:26:19.329 --> 1:26:22.457
And I think probably
the weakness of her showed there.

1:26:22.499 --> 1:26:24.933
Andy was very struck by her.

1:26:24.968 --> 1:26:27.095
Andy would always
invite somebody, to say,

1:26:27.137 --> 1:26:29.105
"Would you want to be
in one of my movies?"

1:26:29.139 --> 1:26:31.903
And of course, Edie took Andy
very seriously on that.

1:26:31.942 --> 1:26:35.400
Who was Edie Sedgwick?
Edie Sedgwick was a combination

1:26:35.445 --> 1:26:38.414
of all the tragic women
who came before her.

1:26:38.448 --> 1:26:41.645
She looked great
in front of a camera.

1:26:41.685 --> 1:26:43.778
And she loved being
in front of one.

1:26:43.820 --> 1:26:46.311
Edie was taken advantage of,

1:26:46.356 --> 1:26:49.553
and hugely because she
was so loving and trusting.

1:26:49.593 --> 1:26:51.060
She was very trusting.

1:26:51.094 --> 1:26:53.358
She looked into your eyes.

1:26:53.397 --> 1:26:55.558
She listened to what
you had to say.

1:26:55.599 --> 1:26:58.568
She made you believe that you were
the most important person

1:26:58.602 --> 1:27:00.729
to her
or on the planet.

1:27:00.771 --> 1:27:03.399
Yeah, I think Edie took on Andy

1:27:03.440 --> 1:27:05.965
as the father
that she didn't have.

1:27:06.009 --> 1:27:08.569
Everybody I know that really
knew her wanted to save her.

1:27:08.612 --> 1:27:11.843
That was one of the things--
trying to keep her off drugs,

1:27:11.882 --> 1:27:14.783
trying to get her
to pull her life together.

1:27:14.818 --> 1:27:18.151
If you said "I love you,"
she just brightened up.

1:27:18.188 --> 1:27:20.452
So you got
an immediate response,

1:27:20.490 --> 1:27:23.254
and I think that's
how she caught people really strongly.

1:27:23.293 --> 1:27:26.285
She had her own sense
of style,

1:27:26.329 --> 1:27:28.297
which no one
had ever seen before.

1:27:28.331 --> 1:27:30.492
She invented
an entirely new look.

1:27:30.534 --> 1:27:33.628
She inspired us all to want
to take care of her.

1:27:33.670 --> 1:27:36.366
But believe me,
that was some job.

1:27:36.406 --> 1:27:38.499
And of course, she had
a terrible time with drugs

1:27:38.542 --> 1:27:41.568
and also the character
that comes with that.

1:27:41.611 --> 1:27:44.842
Endless searching
through her bag to try to find a key

1:27:44.881 --> 1:27:48.078
or to try to find lipstick
or whatever.

1:27:48.118 --> 1:27:50.052
But still
enchanting anyway.
